<!DOCTYPE html>
{# ----------------------------------------------------------------------
   Handoff Report — PDF / HTML companion to templates/handoff/handoff.md.j2

   Same data, same voice rules, polished for buyers who want one file to
   forward. Inherits the visual language from templates/report/report.html.j2
   so the two deliverables read as siblings.
---------------------------------------------------------------------- #}
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <title>{{ customer.app_name }} · LaunchLook Handoff Report</title>
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Fraunces:opsz,wght@9..144,500;9..144,600&family=Inter:wght@400;500;600&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --paper: #FAF7F2;
      --ink: #1F1B16;
      --muted: #6B6359;
      --accent: #B45309;
      --line: #E7E0D6;
      --surface: #FFFFFF;
      --surface-tint: #F4EFE7;
      --critical: #B91C1C;
      --high: #C2410C;
      --medium: #B45309;
      --low: #15803D;
    }

    @page {
      size: A4 portrait;
      margin: 25mm 20mm 22mm 20mm;
    }

    * { box-sizing: border-box; }

    html, body {
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background: var(--paper);
      color: var(--ink);
      font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, sans-serif;
      font-size: 10.5pt;
      line-height: 1.55;
      -webkit-print-color-adjust: exact;
      print-color-adjust: exact;
    }

    .doc-header {
      border-top: 3px solid var(--accent);
      padding-top: 10pt;
      margin-bottom: 14pt;
    }

    .eyebrow {
      font-size: 8pt;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--accent);
      letter-spacing: 0.18em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin: 0;
    }

    h1 {
      font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
      font-weight: 500;
      font-size: 24pt;
      line-height: 1.15;
      margin: 6pt 0 4pt;
      color: var(--ink);
      letter-spacing: -0.005em;
    }

    .subtitle {
      font-size: 10pt;
      color: var(--muted);
      margin: 0 0 6pt;
    }

    .meta-row {
      margin: 12pt 0 14pt;
      padding: 10pt 12pt;
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-left: 3px solid var(--accent);
      border-radius: 4pt;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
      font-size: 9.5pt;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }

    .meta-row strong { color: var(--ink); font-weight: 500; }

    h2 {
      font-family: 'Fraunces', Georgia, serif;
      font-weight: 500;
      font-size: 16pt;
      margin: 18pt 0 8pt;
      padding-bottom: 4pt;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--line);
      page-break-after: avoid;
      color: var(--ink);
    }

    h3.severity-group {
      font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      font-weight: 600;
      font-size: 11pt;
      margin: 14pt 0 6pt;
      color: var(--ink);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    }

    h3.severity-group .count {
      font-weight: 400;
      color: var(--muted);
      text-transform: none;
      letter-spacing: 0;
      margin-left: 6pt;
    }

    .context-paragraph {
      margin: 12pt 0 8pt;
      font-size: 10.5pt;
      line-height: 1.65;
      color: var(--ink);
      white-space: pre-wrap;
    }

    .passed-checks ul {
      list-style: none;
      padding: 0;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .passed-checks li {
      font-size: 10pt;
      color: var(--ink);
      padding: 2pt 0;
    }

    .passed-checks li::before {
      content: "✓ ";
      color: var(--low);
      font-weight: 600;
      margin-right: 4pt;
    }

    .finding {
      margin: 8pt 0;
      padding: 10pt 12pt;
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 4pt;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .finding.high { border-left: 3px solid var(--high); }
    .finding.medium { border-left: 3px solid var(--medium); }
    .finding.low { border-left: 3px solid var(--low); }

    .finding-title {
      font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
      font-size: 11pt;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 0 0 4pt;
      color: var(--ink);
      line-height: 1.3;
    }

    .finding-section {
      margin-top: 6pt;
      font-size: 9.5pt;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .finding-section .label {
      color: var(--ink);
      font-weight: 600;
    }

    .fix-prompt {
      margin-top: 8pt;
      padding: 8pt 10pt;
      background: var(--paper);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 4pt;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .fix-prompt-label {
      font-size: 7.5pt;
      font-weight: 600;
      color: var(--ink);
      letter-spacing: 0.14em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      margin: 0 0 4pt;
    }

    .fix-prompt-body {
      font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', Consolas, 'Courier New', monospace;
      font-size: 8.5pt;
      line-height: 1.5;
      color: var(--ink);
      margin: 0;
      white-space: pre-wrap;
      word-break: break-word;
    }

    .narrative-block {
      margin: 8pt 0;
      padding: 10pt 12pt;
      background: var(--surface);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 4pt;
      font-size: 10pt;
      line-height: 1.6;
      color: var(--ink);
      white-space: pre-wrap;
      page-break-inside: avoid;
    }

    .toolchain ul,
    .didnt-look-at ul {
      margin: 6pt 0;
      padding-left: 18pt;
    }

    .toolchain li,
    .didnt-look-at li {
      font-size: 10pt;
      color: var(--ink);
      padding: 1pt 0;
    }

    .closing {
      margin-top: 22pt;
      padding-top: 12pt;
      border-top: 1px solid var(--line);
      font-size: 9pt;
      color: var(--muted);
      line-height: 1.55;
    }

    .closing a { color: var(--accent); text-decoration: none; }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <header class="doc-header">
    <p class="eyebrow">LaunchLook · Handoff Report</p>
    <h1>{{ customer.app_name }}</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">
      For your next developer · prepared {{ audit_date }}
    </p>
  </header>

  <div class="meta-row">
    <strong>Built with:</strong> {{ customer.builder }}{% if customer.platform %} ({{ customer.platform }}){% endif %}<br />
    <strong>Verdict:</strong> {{ verdict.label or verdict.summary }}{% if verdict.label and verdict.summary %} ({{ verdict.summary }}){% endif %}<br />
    <strong>Audit date:</strong> {{ audit_date }}
  </div>

  <h2>One-paragraph context</h2>
  <p class="context-paragraph">{{ context_paragraph }}</p>

  {% if passed_checks %}
  <section class="passed-checks">
    <h2>What's working</h2>
    <ul>
      {% for check in passed_checks %}
      <li>{{ check }}</li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
  </section>
  {% endif %}

  <h2>What needs fixing</h2>

  {% set severity_groups = [
    ('findings_high', 'Must fix before launch', 'high'),
    ('findings_medium', 'Should fix soon', 'medium'),
    ('findings_low', 'Polish for later', 'low'),
  ] %}

  {% for key, label, css in severity_groups %}
    {% set group = groups[key] %}
    {% if group %}
    <h3 class="severity-group">{{ label }} <span class="count">({{ group|length }})</span></h3>
    {% for f in group %}
    <article class="finding {{ css }}">
      <p class="finding-title">
        {{ f.title }}
      </p>
      {% if f.what_we_saw %}
      <div class="finding-section">
        <span class="label">What we saw.</span> {{ f.what_we_saw }}
      </div>
      {% endif %}
      {% if f.why_it_matters %}
      <div class="finding-section">
        <span class="label">Why it matters.</span> {{ f.why_it_matters }}
      </div>
      {% endif %}
      {% if f.fix_prompt %}
      <div class="fix-prompt">
        <p class="fix-prompt-label">Copy-paste fix prompt</p>
        <p class="fix-prompt-body">{{ f.fix_prompt }}</p>
      </div>
      {% endif %}
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
    {% endif %}
  {% endfor %}

  <h2>Recommended order</h2>
  <div class="narrative-block">{{ recommended_order }}</div>

  {% if code_review_notes %}
  <h2>What we'd flag in a code review</h2>
  <div class="narrative-block">{{ code_review_notes }}</div>
  {% endif %}

  <section class="toolchain">
    <h2>Toolchain &amp; access notes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Builder:</strong> {{ customer.builder }}</li>
      {% if customer.platform %}<li><strong>Platform:</strong> {{ customer.platform }}</li>{% endif %}
      {% if customer.deploy_target %}
      <li><strong>Deploy target:</strong> {{ customer.deploy_target }}</li>
      {% else %}
      <li><strong>Deploy target:</strong> not specified (ask the customer)</li>
      {% endif %}
      {% if customer.integrations %}
      <li><strong>Integrations:</strong> {{ customer.integrations | join(", ") }}</li>
      {% else %}
      <li><strong>Integrations:</strong> not specified (ask the customer)</li>
      {% endif %}
      {% if customer.app_url and not customer.url_redacted %}
      <li><strong>Live URL:</strong> {{ customer.app_url }}</li>
      {% endif %}
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="didnt-look-at">
    <h2>What we DIDN'T look at</h2>
    <p>We didn't audit:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Database schema or queries under load</li>
      <li>Billing logic when scaled past 100 customers</li>
      <li>Security posture against motivated attackers (this is not a pentest)</li>
      <li>Codebase architecture for long-term maintainability</li>
    </ul>
    <p>For any of these, get a developer with that specific specialty. Before processing real payments at volume, get a real pentest.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="closing">
    <p>Generated by LaunchLook &middot; <a href="https://launchlook.app">launchlook.app</a> &middot; Find launch issues before your users do.</p>
  </section>

</body>
</html>
